\cf1\fs28 Ions starting with varying Energies, Angles and Depths\par
\pard\cf0\i\fs22 Examples:\par
\pard\li432\cf2 Calculating Plasma Ions Hitting a Solid\par
Simulating a Receding Surface from Sputtering\par
Simulating Reactor Radiation Damage in Metals\par
\pard\cf0\b0\i0\par
Sometimes users wish to consider incident ions with various energies, with various angles of incidence and possibly starting at various depths. For this application the data file, \cf3\b\i TRIM.DAT\cf0\b0 ,\i0  is used, see Table 1 below. It can be used to simulate the ions from a plasma hitting a surface (various angles and energies), e.g. solar wind effects on planetary materials. It can be used to simulate a receding surface with subsequent ions starting at increasing depths, e.g. from ion sputtering effects. Or it can be used to simulate nuclear reaction processes, e.g. neutron induced alpha-particles created throughout reactor materials.\par
\par
\f1 Examples of typical \cf3\b\i TRIM.DAT \cf0\b0\i0 files are found in the sub-directory \cf3\b\i SRIM Tools \cf0\b0\i0 as files \cf3\b\i TRIM1.DAT \cf0\b0\i0 and \cf3\b\i TRIM2.dat\cf0\b0\i0 . When you construct a \cf3\b\i TRIM.DAT \cf0\b0\i0 file, this file must be placed in the SRIM root directory (which holds the program \cf4\b\i TRIM.exe\cf0\b0\i0 ).\f0\par
