To run your own calculation, make up a new file \cf3\b\i TRIM.DAT\cf0\b0\i0 , then follow the instructions above.\par
You will have to specify your own ion and target. When you prepare the TRIM.DAT file be sure that your editor places \b CR+LF\b0  characters at the end of each line, and at the end of the file there is an \b EOF\b0  character (\b EOF\b0  = End Of File). Most editors do this automatically and these characters are essential. If you finish your calculation and suddenly get Error #62, then your data file is missing the EOF character. \par
